<p>The <code>curl</code> tag makes HTTP requests.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}curl 'https://api.example.com/data'{close}
  {open}$response{close}
{open}/curl{close}</pre>

<h2>Options</h2>
<table border="1" cellpadding="5">
  <tr><th>Option</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td>method</td><td>HTTP method (GET, POST, etc.)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>headers</td><td>Request headers</td></tr>
  <tr><td>data</td><td>POST data</td></tr>
  <tr><td>timeout</td><td>Request timeout</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>Example POST</h2>
<pre>{open}curl 'https://api.example.com/submit', method='POST', data='name=test'{close}
  Response: {open}$body{close}
{open}/curl{close}</pre>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The curl tag requires network access. Examples here are documentation only.</p>
